  title: 入朝告奏表
  author: 金坵
  language: lzh
  text: 上穹云遠切殫臣懇以倍馳北斗所臨猶想帝居而恒仰
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 入朝告奏表
  author: 金坵
  language: lzh
  text: 上穹云遠。切殫臣懇以倍馳。北斗所臨。猶想帝居而恒仰。
korean:
  title: 입조 고주 표
  author: 김구
  language: kor
  text: 하늘이 멀다 하매 신하의 정성을 다하여 더욱더 달리고, 북두(北斗)가 다다른 곳에는 오히려 대궐을 상상하여 항상 우러릅니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0430_010_0180&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Presented Upon Entering Court
  author: Kim Gu
  language: eng
  text: Though heaven stretches distant, my devotion as a subject redoubles my urgency to hasten forth. Wherever the North Star's light falls, still do I envision the imperial palace, my gaze forever lifted in reverence.
  footnotes:
    - The North Star (北斗) traditionally symbolizes the emperor's throne in Chinese and Korean poetry, representing the axis around which all things revolve.
    - The memorial form (表) was a formal petition or statement presented to the throne, typically expressing loyalty and commitment to service.
